  "text": "The HBW version of pursuit strategies is an implementation of those techniques dedicated to approximating by partitioning. It approximates each element of the partition independently of each other but links all the partition's elements by a global constraint on sparsity [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . The approach simply ranks the partition units for their sequential stepwise approximation.",
